1. you need to install git on server via the MobaXterm SSH with the below command
		# yum install git
2. confirm installtion with 
		git --version

3. next go into jenkins gui and download git plugins. search for the plugin that allows you to integrate git with jenkins.
5. next go to global tool configuration. scroll down to configure your path to git executable.
	to get the path direction, enter the below code on your terminal to show the git diection. 
				# whereis git
	it is advisable to leave the path as "git" first, but if this fail, we can change the directory to the copied path generated on the server terminal